{"key":"post-10718640","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10718640</id>\n<content>Ideal pH of a substrate is 5.5 to 6.5, so you don't want to use lime in substrates.&amp;nbsp; Use gypsum only, and it isn't for adjusting pH. Gypsum is for adding calcium and sulfur, both of which aid in fruitbody development, and both of which are usually lacking in most substrates.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10718691</next>\n<prev>10718517</prev>\n<first>10718517</first>\n<last>10719380</last>\n<when>1248245242</when>\n<utime>07/22/09 09:47 AM</utime>\n</post>"}